## Spacing Scale

Base unit: **4px**

Standard scale: `0, 2px, 4px, 6px, 8px, 10px, 12px, 16px, 20px, 24px, 32px, 40px, 48px, 56px, 64px, 72px, 80px`

Non-standard values found (should be rationalized):
- `5px` (top margins on footer)
- `9.6px` (footer margins)
- `11px`, `17px`, `19px`, `22px`, `27px`, `28px`, `30px`, `37px` (footer specifics)

**Recommended approach:** Use multiples of 4px wherever possible. For specific UI sections (footer especially), maintain current non-standard values for now but document them as "footer-legacy" spacing.

## Typography Scale

### Font Families

| Token | Value |
|-------|-------|
| `--sans` | `system-ui, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif` |
| `--heading` | `system-ui, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif` |
| `--mono` | `ui-monospace, Consolas, monospace` |

### Font Sizes

Standard scale: `12px, 14px, 15px, 16px, 17px, 18px, 20px, 24px, 26px, 29px, 32px, 34px, 36px, 37px, 40px, 42px, 50px, 56px, 72px`

| Token | Size | Weight | Usage |
|-------|------|--------|-------|
| `xs` | `12px` | 400 | Footer legal text |
| `sm` | `14px` | 400 | Small labels, buttons, links |
| `sm-md` | `15px` | 400 | Input text, product prices |
| `base` | `16px` | 400 | Body text (root), header, card titles |
| `md` | `17px` | 400 | Product descriptions |
| `lg` | `18px` | 400 | Root font size (desktop) |
| `xl` | `24px` | 600 | Section titles, card titles |
| `2xl` | `32px` | 600 | Featured products title |
| `3xl` | `40px` | 600 | Product detail title (desktop) |
| `4xl` | `50px` | 600 | Hero title |
| `5xl` | `56px` | 600 | Page heading (h1) |
| `6xl` | `72px` | 700 | Large image placeholder text |

### Font Weights

| Weight | Usage |
|--------|-------|
| `400` | Body text, standard text |
| `500` | Headings (h1, h2) |
| `600` | Section titles, card titles, featured links |
| `700` | Primary buttons, eyebrows, product prices, logo text, image placeholders |

## Component Patterns

### Buttons

**Primary Button (Header/CTA)**

.primary-btn {
  background: rgb(0, 93, 171);
  color: #fff;
  border: none;
  padding: 10px 16px;
  font-size: 14px;
  font-weight: 700;
  border-radius: 3px;
  cursor: pointer;
  min-height: 40px;
}

.primary-btn:hover {
  background: rgb(0, 75, 140);
}
```

**Link Button (Text-only)**
```css
.link-btn {
  color: rgb(0, 93, 171);
  background: transparent;
  border: none;
  padding: 0;
  font-size: 14px;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.link-btn:hover {
  color: rgb(0, 75, 140);
  text-decoration: underline;
}
```

### Cards (Product)

**Structure:**
```html
<article class="product-card">
  <a href="/products/..." class="product-card-link" aria-label="...">
    <div class="product-card-media">
      <img class="product-card-image" src="..." alt="..." loading="lazy" />
    </div>
    <div class="product-card-details">
      <h3 class="product-card-title">Title</h3>
      <p class="product-card-description">Description</p>
      <p class="product-card-price">$Price</p>
    </div>
  </a>
</article>
```

**Spacing:** `16px` padding on `.product-card-details`, `20px` gap between cards in grid

### Navigation Items

**Category Dropdown:**
```html
<button class="browse-btn" aria-expanded="false">Browse</button>
<div class="category-dropdown" aria-hidden="true">
  <ul class="category-list">
    <li class="category-item">
      <button class="category-item-btn">Category Name</button>
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>
```

**Utility Links:**
```html
<nav class="utility-nav">
  <ul class="utility-links">
    <li><a href="#" class="utility-link">Link</a></li>
  </ul>
</nav>
```

### Featured Section

**Structure:**
```html
<section class="featured-products" aria-labelledby="featured-products-title">
  <div class="featured-products-header">
    <p class="featured-products-eyebrow">Eyebrow text</p>
    <h2 class="featured-products-title" id="featured-products-title">Shop Category</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="featured-products-grid">
    <!-- product cards here -->
  </div>
</section>
```

**Spacing:** `56px 32px 64px` padding

## Rules

1. **Never use hardcoded hex/rgb/hsl color values** — use CSS variables (`--text`, `--bg`, etc.) or design token references. Exception: Primary blue (`rgb(0, 93, 171)`) and link blues are currently hardcoded; these should be converted to `--primary-blue` in a future refactor.

2. **Typography** — Use font sizes from the standard scale. Avoid one-off sizes like `13px` or `15px` unless they are in the approved scale.

3. **Spacing** — Use values from the 4px base scale: `4px, 8px, 12px, 16px, 20px, 24px, 32px, 40px, 48px, 56px, 64px, 72px, 80px`. Legacy footer spacing (5px, 9.6px, 11px, 17px, 19px, 22px, 27px, 28px, 30px, 37px) should remain unchanged for now.

4. **Components** — Follow the documented class naming conventions:
   - Use semantic class names (e.g., `.product-card`, not `.card-1`)
   - Group related classes with a shared prefix (e.g., `.product-card-*`)
   - Structure HTML to match documented patterns

5. **Font weights** — Use `400` for body, `500` for headings, `600` for section titles, `700` for buttons and eyebrows.

6. **Responsiveness** — Maintain existing media query breakpoints (`max-width: 1024px` for tablet, implied mobile-first approach). Do not add new breakpoints without design review.

7. **Fonts** — All sans-serif text uses `var(--sans)`; all monospace uses `var(--mono)`. Do not introduce new font families.
